### Exporting an agent and its dependencies

An agent, along with all of its tools and workflows, can be exported from one
cluster and imported into another. This is useful for promoting agents between
environments (e.g. dev to prod).

The export configuration uses the `elasticstack_kibana_export_ab_agent` data
source to fetch the agent and all its dependencies into a single output.
Run this in a separate Terraform root module pointed at the **source** cluster.

{{ tffile "examples/resources/elasticstack_kibana_ab_agent/export.tf" }}

### Importing an agent from the exported state

The import configuration reads the export state and recreates the agent with
all its tools and workflows on the **target** cluster. Readonly (built-in)
tools are skipped since they already exist. Workflow-type tools automatically
get their `workflow_id` replaced with the newly created workflow's ID.

{{ tffile "examples/resources/elasticstack_kibana_ab_agent/import.tf" }}

